name: clangdev
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "5.0.0" %}
{% set github = "isuruf/clang" %}

{% set sha256 = "6896f6aa2e7ec7133aa4101ba899c9e9b6cf8c7d40f2c12ba19a22f6ae77baf2" %}
{% set revision = "9826991e2bdc60b8f40253af0481ed6e74832ceb" %}

{% set clang_variant = "flang" %}
{% set build_number = "2" %}

package:
  name: clangdev
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: cfe-{{ version }}.src.tar.xz
  url: https://github.com/{{ github }}/archive/{{ revision }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}
  patches:
    # https://github.com/pocl/pocl/issues/1
    - disable-libxml2-detection.patch  # [linux]

build:
  number: {{ build_number }}
  string: {{ clang_variant }}_{{ build_number  }}
  skip: true  # [py<36 or osx]

  features:
    - flang
    - vc14    # [win and py36]

requirements:
  build:
    - toolchain
    - cmake >=3.4.3

    # Needed to unpack the source tarball
    - m2-xz  # [py27 and win32]
    - m2w64-xz  # [py27 and win64]

    - system  # [linux and not armv7l]

    # "compiling .pyc files" fails without this:
    - python

    - llvmdev =={{ version }}
    - libxml2 2.9.*

  run:
    - vs2015_runtime  # [win]

test:
  requires:
    - python {{ environ['PY_VER'] + '*' }}  # [win]
    - cmake >=3.4.3
    - flang-meta
  files:
    - mytest.c
  commands:
    - $PREFIX/bin/clang --version  # [unix]
    - $PREFIX/bin/clang++ --version  # [unix]
    - $PREFIX/bin/clang-check --version  # [unix]

    - $PREFIX/bin/clang -v -c mytest.c      # [unix]
    - "%LIBRARY_BIN%/clang -v -c mytest.c"  # [win]

    - if not exist %LIBRARY_INC%\\clang\\Lex\\Lexer.h exit 1  # [win]
    - test -f $PREFIX/include/clang/Lex/Lexer.h      # [unix]
    - test -f $PREFIX/lib/libclangBasic.a            # [unix]

about:
  home: http://llvm.org/
  license: NCSA
  license_file: LICENSE.TXT
  summary: Development headers and libraries for Clang

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - inducer
    - jakirkham
    - mattwala
    - SylvainCorlay

about.summary: Development headers and libraries for Clang
